summary: SummaryNARS Powermatte High Intensity Lip Pencil is a fully loaded matte lip formula charged with up to 12-hour staying power. Transformative cream-to-matte texture applies effortlessly and seals in a bold, matte finish. Choose from 13 power shades and let lips dry down fully for transfer-proof results.
details: DetailsBenefitsTransformative cream-to-matte texture applies effortlessly and seals in a bold, matte finishSharpenable pencil format allows for precise application packed with pigmentUp to 12-hour wearTransfer-proofAll-day comfortOne swipe, instant colorKey IngredientsPower Pigment Complex - a dynamic blend of pure pigments and color-locking ingredients - saturates lips with dense color that glides effortlessly and wears comfortablyFormulated WithoutParabensSulfatesPhthalatesMineral OilItem 2615129How To UseUsing the tip of the pencil, line lips first before filling in with color to create a bold, matte look.Try lining lips with one shade, then filling in color with a lighter shade for a fuller look with added dimension.Allow formula to dry down fully for transfer-proof color.Sharpen before each use with NARS Pencil Sharpener (sold separately) for best results.IngredientsDimethicone, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Caprylyl Methicone, Octyldodecanol, Synthetic Wax, Lauroyl Lysine, Dicalcium Phosphate, Phenylpropyldimethylsiloxysilicate, Diisostearyl Malate, Polyethylene, Copernicia Cerifera (Carnauba) Wax/Cera Carnauba/Cire De Carnauba, Stearyl Heptanoate, Stearyl Caprylate, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Polyhydroxystearic Acid, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Isostearic Acid, Lecithin, Polyglyceryl-3 Polyricinoleate, Propylene Carbonate, [+/-(May Contain/Peut Contenir): Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Red 6 (CI 15850), Red 7 Lake (CI 15850), Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Yellow 6 Lake (CI 15985), Red 28 Lake (CI 45410)].Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Using the tip of the pencil, line lips first before filling in with color to create a bold, matte look.Try lining lips with one shade, then filling in color with a lighter shade for a fuller look with added dimension.Allow formula to dry down fully for transfer-proof color.Sharpen before each use with NARS Pencil Sharpener (sold separately) for best results.
ingredients: Copernicia Cerifera (Carnauba) Wax/Cera Carnauba/Cire De Carnauba

reviews.headline: Moisturizing pencil with bold, flattering color
reviews.comments: Love this lip pencil- it does not feel dry on your lips and is so easy to apply while also giving so much color. You really don't need to add any gloss, etc and can just use this if you want.  I bought two colors and will go back to buy a third because the color choices are universally flattering. They provide a great amount of color, but not overwhelming.

reviews.headline: Good until it wasn't
reviews.comments:
I was using shade Cruella as a lip liner and loved it up until it just fell out of the tube unwarranted when I was applying. 

Otherwise it works great! The color pay off is great. Only thing is that it does smudge easily, so trying to clean it up as a liner gets a little obnoxious.

reviews.headline: New formula downgrade
reviews.comments:
I agree with other reviews about the new formula being too slippery. I went through 8 lip pencils from the old formula. This is my first purchase with the new formula and even the color is slightly different. 

I wasnt even aware that the formula changed, I thought I might've purchased a different product.

reviews.headline: Pales in comparison pro old formula
reviews.comments: I love the old formula of these lip pencils but the new formula is way too slippery, goes outside the lines qnd transfers everywhere. The old formula stays on sooooo much longer and is wayyyyy more user friendly

reviews.headline: I Love This Lip Pencil
reviews.comments: Fantastic lip pencil!

reviews.headline: Improved Formula
reviews.comments: I was a fan of the old velvet matte pencil and used Cruella and Dragon girl for nearly a decade, so when I found out they were being discontinued I was quite unhappy. so naturally I was very skeptical with this new formula, however after using it for some months now, I find that this is the lip I reach for most and bought more shades. It goes on very smooth and pigmented and dries down to a matte finish. They wear well through drinking and snacking but if you eat a meal, you'll have to reapply. They're extremely comfortable and don't dry out the lips. What I love the most, is the nuanced shades. Walkyrie and Bohemian Rhapsody are stunning and unique to my collection, and pair well together for an ombre effect. Cruella and Dragon girl are just as beautiful and the shades have not changed, thank goodness. The new red they released called Midnight Rider is now my all time favorite red and it's truly perfection.

reviews.headline: Not sure why NARS is so expensive
reviews.comments: I used the Powermatte High Intensity Lip Pencil and it in no way lasted 12 hours. I let it sit for a solid hour, took a sip of coffee and it transferred to the mug. NARS is underwhelming and overpriced. Don't waste your money. MAC is better

reviews.headline: Does not stay on
reviews.comments: I would not purchase this product again. It does not last at all and for it costing $$ I expected a lot more.

reviews.headline: Wonderful purchase!!
reviews.comments: Love the color!!! The staying power and the coverage were outstanding!!! Love putting this on!!!

reviews.headline: Nars velvet matte was so much better!
reviews.comments: I wore Nars velvet matte lip pencil in do ke baby for as long as i can remember. It's the only lip product I have ever received complements on. Lasted all day and I would only add a clear balm to spruce up. When I heard it was discontinued I was heartbroken. Looking on the website the new pencil says "american woman" is a chestnut rose. Same description for Nars Do Me Baby. It is not even close. Do Me Baby was a perfect my lips but better. American Woman is ORANGE. Do not waste your money.

reviews.headline: This crayon is no longer what it once was
reviews.comments:
Why is it that companies, are cutting costs so deeply, that they're messing with old formulas and taking away the magic?

This was my fav lip crayon on the planet, FOR YEARS!! Stupid Nars, decided to change the formula and colors. Its not good. My crayon is heading back to ulta asap. 

Come on Nars!! Bring back the old lip crayon! Youve made this new formula SO CHEAP!! Ugh!

reviews.headline: Not for me
reviews.comments: I was super excited about this lipstick when i originally tried it at the store, but after wearing it for one night out (to a wedding) I felt like I had to keep reapplying all night long! And at the end of the night my lips were so dry. Usually love Nars but this wasnt it for me!

reviews.headline: Yes get this
reviews.comments: Loved the color and ease of applying. I am ordering another one.

reviews.headline: Absolutely shocked
reviews.comments: I received a free trial of this pencil in the color _, and it honestly sat on my shelf for weeks. I know how these lio pencils usually go - they look half decent when applied, smear in 15 minutes, and have completely disappeared in just a few hours. I was staying in one night and decided to give it a try with very low expectations. When I tell you this color did not BUDGE. It was easier for me to apply then a liquid (3 minutes vs the usual 10-15 fixing symmetry issues), the formula is light and soft, and even on my VERY DRY (I biteâ€¦) lips, didnt crumble or flake or smear. I wore this to every Christmas party, and hours of food and drink later, it still looked amazing.  I'm going to start my collection in every color

reviews.headline: Loved original product reformulation is horrible
reviews.comments: I love this product I repurchased so many times. They reformulated and it changed everything. Dolce Vita was the perfect color for me. Now its too pink. So sad I wont repurchase.

faceoff_positive.comments: I recently tried the NARS Matte Lip Pencil, and I'm absolutely thrilled with the results! This lip pencil has quickly become my go-to for a stunning matte finish and long-lasting color.    First and foremost, the texture is impeccable. It glides on smoothly without any tugging or pulling, allowing for precise application. The matte finish is velvety and luxurious, giving my lips a sophisticated look that lasts for hours.    One of the standout features of this product is its incredible color payoff. The pigment is rich and vibrant, and a single swipe is enough to achieve a bold, intense lip look. Plus, it stays put throughout the day, even through meals and drinks.    Another bonus is the convenient pencil design. It makes application a breeze, and the built-in sharpener ensures that I can maintain the perfect point for precise lines and filling in my lips.    I also appreciate the wide range of shades available in the NARS Matte Lip Pencil collection. Whether you're looking for a classic red, a subtle nude, or a trendy berry tone, there's a shade for every occasion and mood.    In terms of comfort, this lip pencil doesn't disappoint. It doesn't feel dry or cakey on the lips, and I don't experience any feathering or smudging.    Overall, the NARS Matte Lip Pencil is a must-have in any makeup collection. It combines a luxurious matte finish, intense color, and long-lasting wear in a user-friendly pencil form. I highly recommend it for anyone looking to elevate their lip game with a touch of elegance. As a busy mom of three having two products in one that can be used so quick and effortlessly is a no brainer. It's a makeup essential that I can't live without!
faceoff_positive.headline: A busy mom must have

faceoff_negative.comments: I had never tried any NARS lipsticks before, as this product was my very first impression of any NARS lip products. Right from the application, I could see the shade was much richer and brighter than the shade on the packaging. The color truly is a passionate red tone though. When I applied this lipstick on my lips, although it was very pigmented, it was also messy. I feel the lipstick could smear everywhere if you let it. Luckily I only applied the lipstick in the inside portions of my lips and used a lipliner but If I hadn't, the lipstick would definitely bleed outside my lip lines. So apply with caution. I did notice that it does somewhat dry down on the lips, not super dry but dry enough not to continue moving and feeling "messy".
faceoff_negative.headline: Cute But messy
